To write a PHP function that retrieves the definition of a given phrase and filters out any vulgar language or inappropriate content, you can use an API like the Oxford Dictionaries API or the WordsAPI. Below is a sample code snippet that demonstrates how to implement this functionality:

```php
function getDefinition($phrase) {
    // Replace with your actual API key and endpoint
    $apiKey = 'YOUR_API_KEY';
    $url = "https://api.wordsapi.com/v2/{$phrase}/definitions";

    // Initialize cURL session
    $ch = curl_init();

    curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, $url);
    curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
    curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, [
        "Authorization: Bearer {$apiKey}"
    ]);

    // Execute cURL request
    $response = curl_exec($ch);

   if (curl_errno($ch)) {
        return 'Error: ' . curl_error($ch);
   }

   // Close cURL session
   curl_close($ch);

   // Decode JSON response
   $data = json_decode($response);

   if (isset($data->definitions) && !empty($data->definitions)) {
       foreach ($data->definitions as $definition) {
           if (!containsVulgarLanguage(strtolower(trim(strip_tags($definition->text))))) {
               return trim(strip_tags(($definition->text)));
           }
       }
       return "No appropriate definitions found.";
   } else {
       return "Definition not found.";
   }
}

function containsVulgarLanguage(string $text): bool {
     // List of vulgar words to filter out; expand as needed.
     $vulgarWords = ['badword1', 'badword2', 'offensiveTerm'];

     foreach ($vulgarWords as $word) {
         if (stripos($text, strtolower(trim(preg_replace('/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/', '',$word)))) !== false) { 
             return true;
         }
     }

     return false;
}

// Example usage:
echo getDefinition("kick the bucket");
```

Make sure to replace `'YOUR_API_KEY'` with your actual API key from the chosen dictionary service. The `containsVulgarLanguage` function checks for predefined vulgar terms in each definition returned by the API. Adjust and expand this list based on your requirements.

